org.turbogwt.core.collections.client

Class LightSet<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<T>
        • org.turbogwt.core.collections.client.LightSet<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of set values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, Set<T>

    public class LightSet<T>
extends AbstractSet<T>
    A fast implementation of Set indexed by a String representation of the object.

    This class indexes objects by resorting to Object.toString().
    Additionally, you can provide a implementation of LightSet.AsString to generate the string representation.
    In order to use it correctly, T should implement toString, so that t.toString().equals(otherT.toString()) is equivalent to t.equals(otherT).
    The same is expected for the LightSet.AsString behavior when provided.

    Author:
    Danilo Reinert
